rian Wright]] || Family || [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0100915/ IMDb]\n|-\n| ''The Wonderful World of Dogs'' || || || ||\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[1990 in Australia]]\n* [[1990 in Australian television]]\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Countries/Australia/ Australian film] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n\n{{Cinema of Australia}}\n{{Films by country}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Australian Films Of 1990}}\n[[Category:Lists of Australian films by year|1990]]\n[[Category:Lists of 1990 films by country or language]]\n[[Category:1990 in Australian cinema|Films]]\n", "name_user": "Bradv", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removing link(s):Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Robyn Gibbesclosed as delete (XFDcloser)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Australian_films_of_1990"}
{"title_page": "Gregory Apps", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Greg Apps\n|image = \n|caption =\n| birthname   = Gregory Richard Apps\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1955|8|21}}\n| birth_place  = \n| othername   = \n| occupation  = Casting director; actor\n| yearsactive = 1973 to present\n| spouse      = Robyn Gibbes\n| education = [[Newington College]]\n| website     = [https://gregappscasting.com.au/ Greg Apps Casting]\n}}\n\n'''Gregory Richard \"Greg\" Apps''' is an [[Australian]] film casting consultant and actor.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0032487/ IMDB Gregory Apps Casting Director | Actor] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref> He cast [[Russell Crowe]], [[Guy Pearce]], [[Eric Bana]], [[Sam Worthington]], and [[Hugo Weaving]] in the roles that brought them to wide public recognition.<ref>[https://www.backstage.com/magazine/author/greg-apps/ Backstage Casting] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nApps was born in 1955 and from 1967 until 1973 he attended [[Newington College]].<ref>Newington College Register of Past Students 1863-1998 (Syd, 1999) pp5</ref>In the 1970s Apps began his working life as an actor. He appeared in the films [[The Chant of Jimmie Blacksmith (film)|The Chant of Jimmie Blacksmith]], [[Mad Dog Morgan]] and [[Sunday Too Far Away]] and on stage in the original Melbourne/Adelaide production of ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]''. In 1982 he first started casting at the [[ABC (Australian TV channel)|ABC Melbourne]]. He has since cast TV commercials, TV series and over 70 feature films. For seven years he was on the board of the [[Australian Film Institute]] and he is the current president of the [[Casting Guild of Australia]].<ref>[https://artsreview.com.au/on-the-couch-with-greg-apps/ Arts Review On the Couch with Greg Apps] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref> Apps is married to Australian actress and casting director Robyn Gibbes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Apps, Greg}}\n[[Category:Casting directors]]\n[[Category:People from Sydney]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:People educated at Newington College]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Greg Apps\n|image = \n|caption =\n| birthname   = Gregory Richard Apps\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1955|8|21}}\n| birth_place  = \n| othername   = \n| occupation  = Casting director; actor\n| yearsactive = 1973 to present\n| spouse      = [[Robyn Gibbes]]\n| education = [[Newington College]]\n| website     = [https://gregappscasting.com.au/ Greg Apps Casting]\n}}\n\n'''Gregory Richard \"Greg\" Apps''' is an [[Australian]] film casting consultant and actor.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0032487/ IMDB Gregory Apps Casting Director | Actor] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref> He cast [[Russell Crowe]], [[Guy Pearce]], [[Eric Bana]], [[Sam Worthington]], and [[Hugo Weaving]] in the roles that brought them to wide public recognition.<ref>[https://www.backstage.com/magazine/author/greg-apps/ Backstage Casting] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nApps was born in 1955 and from 1967 until 1973 he attended [[Newington College]].<ref>Newington College Register of Past Students 1863-1998 (Syd, 1999) pp5</ref>In the 1970s Apps began his working life as an actor. He appeared in the films [[The Chant of Jimmie Blacksmith (film)|The Chant of Jimmie Blacksmith]], [[Mad Dog Morgan]] and [[Sunday Too Far Away]] and on stage in the original Melbourne/Adelaide production of ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]''. In 1982 he first started casting at the [[ABC (Australian TV channel)|ABC Melbourne]]. He has since cast TV commercials, TV series and over 70 feature films. For seven years he was on the board of the [[Australian Film Institute]] and he is the current president of the [[Casting Guild of Australia]].<ref>[https://artsreview.com.au/on-the-couch-with-greg-apps/ Arts Review On the Couch with Greg Apps] Retrieved 16 November 2019.</ref> Apps is married to Australian actress and casting director [[Robyn Gibbes]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Apps, Greg}}\n[[Category:Casting directors]]\n[[Category:People from Sydney]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:People educated at Newington College]]\n", "name_user": "Bradv", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removing link(s):Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Robyn Gibbesclosed as delete (XFDcloser)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregory_Apps"}
